<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-48-0090 </DOCNO><TEXT>Worker exposure to asbestos were surveyed on August 12, 1976, at TuffyService Center (SIC-7539) in Sharonville, Ohio. The number of employeeswas not reported. General area air samples contained 0.008 to 0.02 fibersof asbestos greater than 5 microns per cubic centimeter (f/cc), wellbelow the OSHA Standard of 2.0 f/cc. The author notes that a potentialdoes exist for hazardous exposure to asbestos, and recommends strictcompliance with OSHA Standards for handling abestos.</TEXT></DOC>